Okay.

23:41.004 --> 23:42.381
"Aleister Crowley."

23:47.803 --> 23:50.097
"Some men are born sodomites,

23:50.097 --> 23:54.560
some achieve sodomy
and some have sodomy thrust upon them."

23:58.522 --> 24:00.774
What? This will sell
for at least ten thousand.

24:01.775 --> 24:02.776
How?

24:03.443 --> 24:05.821
- Okay.
- <i>The find of his life,</i>

24:05.821 --> 24:10.158
- <i>and no one there to share the news.</i>
- Wow. That is crazy.

24:11.577 --> 24:13.662
<i>Apollo Kagwa missed her.</i>

25:33.200 --> 25:34.368
Apollo.

25:34.368 --> 25:35.494
Dad?

25:37.037 --> 25:38.038
Dad?

25:38.580 --> 25:39.581
Dad?

26:36.889 --> 26:38.974
"A baby is a dream made real.

26:38.974 --> 26:40.893
But dreams
are the fairies' favorite meal."

26:43.103 --> 26:45.272
<i>Apollo had always loved reading,</i>

26:45.272 --> 26:47.858
<i>but when he held this one,
it was different.</i>

26:55.115 --> 26:56.825
That was your father's box.

26:58.535 --> 27:00.537
Apollo, where did you find this box?

27:02.956 --> 27:04.041
You're coming with me.

27:19.723 --> 27:20.724
Shit.

27:31.068 --> 27:32.402
<i>I'm coming home tomorrow.</i>

27:32.402 --> 27:34.321
<i>My flight doesn't arrive
until late at night,</i>

27:34.321 --> 27:36.990
<i>and you might not even be interested
in seeing me anymore,</i>

27:36.990 --> 27:41.745
<i>but if you were, I'd love your face
to be the first one I find in arrivals.</i>

27:47.292 --> 27:48.293
Thank you.

27:50.963 --> 27:55.175
<i>Attention, passengers
on flight 873 with service to Munich,</i>

27:55.175 --> 27:58.762
<i>your gate has been changed to 540.</i>

28:10.858 --> 28:16.029
<i>Will passenger A. Dos Santos come
to the arrival information desk.</i>

28:49.563 --> 28:50.564
You waited.

28:59.698 --> 29:00.824
All right.

29:00.824 --> 29:02.784
When I got to Salvador,

29:02.784 --> 29:06.079
I stayed with a family
in a neighborhood called Itapuã.

29:06.079 --> 29:09.750
There was a lake there, a lagoon,
called Lagoa do Abaeté.

29:11.001 --> 29:13.921
They told me not to go,
but I didn't listen.

29:41.365 --> 29:44.743
They told you not to come.
And yet, here you are.

29:45.536 --> 29:46.870
Why is that?

29:49.289 --> 29:51.333
Because I am not frightened.

29:52.501 --> 29:54.169
You should be.

29:54.920 --> 29:57.297
Three wishes. For your life. Emma.

29:59.383 --> 30:01.426
How do you know my name?

30:13.105 --> 30:16.316
Three wishes,
before these three knots are tied.

30:21.488 --> 30:22.614
For now.

30:26.368 --> 30:27.870
After.

30:30.914 --> 30:33.333
And beyond.

30:36.253 --> 30:38.630
Be careful what you wish for, Emma.

30:45.929 --> 30:46.930
Yes.

30:53.604 --> 30:54.771
Don't cut!

30:57.191 --> 31:00.694
<i>One must be so careful
what one wishes for.</i>

31:04.781 --> 31:08.368
When it falls off my wrist,
those three wishes will come true.

31:09.536 --> 31:11.830
Do not cut it. <i>Não corta-la</i>.

31:17.711 --> 31:19.588
- That's what she said.
- You're weird.

31:19.588 --> 31:23.592
So this thing's been on my skin
for more than six months.

31:24.718 --> 31:25.969
Let me see.

31:27.679 --> 31:29.389
It does look sturdy.

31:29.389 --> 31:30.724
But you know what?

31:31.934 --> 31:35.062
I am the god Apollo.

31:46.365 --> 31:47.866
<i>Começou.</i>

31:56.959 --> 32:01.463
Emma, with me, all three of your wishes
will come true.

32:04.174 --> 32:05.175
I promise.

32:10.013 --> 32:11.223
You may kiss the bride.

33:08.864 --> 33:11.575
